@page "/agents/loss-adjuster"

<PageTitle>Loss Adjuster Agent — Claims Team in a Day</PageTitle>

<div class="agent-header" style="--accent: #f59e0b">
    <a class="back-link" href="/"><span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to claims office</a>
    <div class="agent-header-row">
        <div class="agent-header-icon">🔍</div>
        <div>
            <div class="agent-header-dept">Loss Adjusting</div>
            <h1>Loss Adjuster Agent</h1>
            <div class="agent-header-persona">Lara — Loss Adjuster</div>
            <p class="tagline">On-the-ground investigator for complex or high-value losses.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="agent-tab-scope" style="--accent: #f59e0b">
    <nav class="agent-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Loss Adjuster agent details">
        <button type="button" class="agent-tab active" data-tab="overview" role="tab" aria-selected="true" tabindex="0">Overview</button>
        <button type="button" class="agent-tab" data-tab="try" role="tab" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">Try it out</button>
    </nav>

    <div class="agent-tab-panel active" data-panel="overview" role="tabpanel">
    <section class="panel" style="--accent: #f59e0b">
        <h2>What this agent does</h2>
        <p>
            Prepares inspection briefs, reviews damage evidence, and drafts a scope of loss
            for human loss adjusters to confirm in the field.
        </p>
        <div class="two-col">
            <div>
                <h3>Responsibilities</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Analyse damage photos, plumber/contractor reports, and quotes.</li>
                    <li>Build an inspection checklist for the human adjuster.</li>
                    <li>Draft the scope of loss and likely cause.</li>
                    <li>Compare contractor quotes against cost benchmarks.</li>
                    <li>Highlight pre-existing damage or underinsurance risks.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Tools available</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>analyzeQuote</strong> — fetch &amp; parse a contractor quote (MCP)</li>
                    <li><strong>compareQuotes</strong> — comparison table + Mermaid totals chart (MCP)</li>
                    <li><strong>generateClaimExcel</strong> — write an .xlsx workbook for the case (MCP)</li>
                    <li>Image / document analysis (Document Intelligence)</li>
                    <li>Inspection checklist generator</li>
                    <li>Cost benchmark lookup</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Sample input quotes</h3>
                <ul class="sample-list">
                    <li><a href="/loss-adjuster/samples/quote-acme-restoration.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener">quote-acme-restoration.json</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/loss-adjuster/samples/quote-bayside-build.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener">quote-bayside-build.json</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/loss-adjuster/samples/quote-sunrise-home.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener">quote-sunrise-home.json</a></li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Human approval</h3>
                <p class="approval">
                    Required for the final loss report, large-loss findings, disputed cause,
                    underinsurance issues, or safety concerns.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel" style="--accent: #f59e0b">
        <h2>How this agent helps with the claim</h2>
        <div class="demo">
            <p>
                For more complex or higher-value losses, Lara's loss-adjuster agent takes the
                photos, contractor reports, and quotes from the claim file and prepares a complete
                inspection brief — what to measure, what to photograph, and what to verify on
                site. It drafts a likely scope of loss and benchmarks the supplier quote against
                comparable jobs in the region.
            </p>
            <p>
                A human loss adjuster takes that brief into the field and confirms or amends
                the scope. Standard low-complexity losses are triaged out so the human team's
                site visits stay focused on the cases that genuinely need a pair of eyes on the
                ground.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    </div>

    <div class="agent-tab-panel" data-panel="try" role="tabpanel">
    <section class="panel adjuster-panel" style="--accent: #f59e0b">
        <h2>Try It Out — Loss Adjuster Demo</h2>
        <p class="muted adjuster-help">
            Walk through how Lara's loss-adjuster agent picks up a complex or
            higher-value claim that Claims Intake has just lodged, reviews the
            evidence on file, and drafts an inspection brief and adjuster report
            with a recommended reserve. All steps run live against the
            <code>/loss-adjuster/*</code> endpoints in this app.
        </p>

        <!-- Step 1 — pick a claim -->
        <div class="adjuster-step" data-step="1">
            <div class="adjuster-step-head">
                <span class="adjuster-step-num">1</span>
                <h3>Pick a claim</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="muted">
                Lara works from the queue of claims already lodged by Iris's
                Claims Intake Agent. Pick one of the claim cases held in memory
                for this demo.
            </p>
            <div class="adjuster-claim-row">
                <select id="adjuster-claim-select" aria-label="Claim ID">
                    <option value="">— Select a claim —</option>
                </select>
                <button type="button" id="adjuster-refresh-btn" class="adjuster-secondary"
                        title="Reload the list of claims">↻ Refresh</button>
            </div>
            <p class="muted adjuster-empty" id="adjuster-empty" hidden>
                No claims yet. Run the
                <a href="/agents/claims-intake">Claims Intake Try It Out</a>
                tab first to lodge a claim, then come back here.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 — review the claim case -->
        <div class="adjuster-step" data-step="2" id="adjuster-claim-card-step" hidden>
            <div class="adjuster-step-head">
                <span class="adjuster-step-num">2</span>
                <h3>Review the claim case</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="muted">Captured by Iris on intake. Lara's agent will work this case in the field.</p>
            <div class="adjuster-claim-card" id="adjuster-claim-card">
                <div class="adjuster-claim-num" id="adjuster-claim-num"></div>
                <div class="adjuster-claim-grid">
                    <div><span class="k">Customer</span><span id="adjuster-claim-customer"></span></div>
                    <div><span class="k">Policy</span><span id="adjuster-claim-policy"></span></div>
                    <div><span class="k">Claim type</span><span id="adjuster-claim-type"></span></div>
                    <div><span class="k">Incident date</span><span id="adjuster-claim-date"></span></div>
                    <div class="span-2"><span class="k">Incident location</span><span id="adjuster-claim-location"></span></div>
                    <div class="span-2"><span class="k">Description</span><span id="adjuster-claim-desc"></span></div>
                    <div><span class="k">Estimated loss</span><span id="adjuster-claim-loss"></span></div>
                    <div><span class="k">Urgency</span><span id="adjuster-claim-urgency"></span></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 — engage the agent -->
        <div class="adjuster-step" data-step="3" id="adjuster-process-step" hidden>
            <div class="adjuster-step-head">
                <span class="adjuster-step-num">3</span>
                <h3>Engage Loss Adjuster Agent</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="muted">
                The agent loads the selected claim's details, reviews the
                available report and site evidence, validates scope and quantum,
                and produces a structured Loss Adjuster Report with a
                recommended reserve.
            </p>
            <button id="adjuster-process-btn" type="button" disabled>Process with Loss Adjuster Agent</button>
            <div id="adjuster-process-status" class="adjuster-status" hidden></div>

            <div class="engage-tabs-scope" data-engage-role="loss-adjuster">
                <div class="engage-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <button type="button" class="engage-tab-btn active" data-engage-tab="narrative">Agent Narrative</button>
                    <button type="button" class="engage-tab-btn" data-engage-tab="reference">Reference</button>
                    <button type="button" class="engage-tab-btn" data-engage-tab="prompt">Agent Prompt &amp; Tools</button>
                    <button type="button" class="engage-tab-btn" data-engage-tab="input">Agent Input</button>
                    <button type="button" class="engage-tab-btn" data-engage-tab="output">Raw Output</button>
                </div>

                <div class="engage-tab-panel active" data-engage-tab="narrative">
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Agent narrative (streamed)</h4>
                        <div class="agent-md engage-narrative-body"><div class="engage-empty">Engage the agent to see the streamed narrative.</div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="engage-tab-panel" data-engage-tab="reference">
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Reference documents cited by the agent</h4>
                        <div class="engage-references-body"><div class="engage-empty">Engage the agent to see the reference documents cited in its response.</div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="engage-tab-panel" data-engage-tab="prompt">
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Agent metadata</h4>
                        <div class="engage-info-meta engage-meta"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>System prompt</h4>
                        <pre class="engage-pre engage-prompt-body">Loading…</pre>
                    </div>
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Tools available</h4>
                        <ul class="engage-tools-list"><li class="engage-empty">Loading…</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="engage-tab-panel" data-engage-tab="input">
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Prompt sent to the agent</h4>
                        <pre class="engage-pre engage-input-body engage-empty">Engage the agent to capture the input that was sent.</pre>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="engage-tab-panel" data-engage-tab="output">
                    <div class="engage-info-block">
                        <h4>Raw agent output (text, citations, every output item including tool / function calls)</h4>
                        <div class="json-viewer engage-output-body"><div class="engage-empty">Engage the agent to see the full raw response.</div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4 — chat with the agent + references -->
        <div class="adjuster-step" data-step="4" id="adjuster-chat-step" hidden>
            <div class="adjuster-step-head">
                <span class="adjuster-step-num">4</span>
                <h3>Chat with Loss Adjuster Agent</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="muted">
                Ask Lara's agent follow-up questions about the loss, the
                inspection brief, the supplier quotes, or anything else on the
                claim. The conversation continues from the initial report,
                so the agent keeps full context.
            </p>

            <div class="adjuster-chat-layout">
                <div class="adjuster-chat-col">
                    <div class="adjuster-chat-messages" id="adjuster-chat-messages" role="log" aria-live="polite">
                        <div class="adjuster-chat-empty">No follow-up messages yet. Ask a question below.</div>
                    </div>
                    <form class="adjuster-chat-form" id="adjuster-chat-form" autocomplete="off">
                        <input type="text" id="adjuster-chat-input"
                               placeholder="Ask a follow-up question (e.g. 'Which quote line items look inflated?')"
                               aria-label="Follow-up question to the Loss Adjuster Agent" />
                        <button type="submit" id="adjuster-chat-send" disabled>Send</button>
                    </form>
                    <div id="adjuster-chat-status" class="adjuster-status" hidden></div>
                </div>

                <aside class="adjuster-refs-col" aria-label="Bing search and document references">
                    <div class="adjuster-refs-head">
                        <h4>References</h4>
                        <span class="adjuster-refs-count" id="adjuster-refs-count">0</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="adjuster-refs-help">
                        Bing search results and document citations the agent
                        used to ground its answers. Updated after every reply.
                    </p>
                    <div class="adjuster-refs-list" id="adjuster-refs-list">
                        <div class="adjuster-refs-empty">References from the agent will appear here.</div>
                    </div>
                </aside>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .adjuster-panel { --adjuster-accent: #f59e0b; }
    .adjuster-help { margin-bottom: 0.9rem; }
    .adjuster-help code { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.12); padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; }

    .adjuster-step {
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.18);
        background: rgba(15, 22, 38, 0.4);
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 0.95rem 1.1rem 1rem 1.1rem;
        margin-top: 0.9rem;
    }
    .adjuster-step-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem; margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
    .adjuster-step-head h3 { margin: 0; color: #fff; font-size: 1rem; }
    .adjuster-step-num {
        display: inline-grid; place-items: center;
        width: 1.55rem; height: 1.55rem;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 22%, rgba(20, 28, 46, 0.7));
        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 55%, transparent);
        color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700;
    }
    .adjuster-step .muted { color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6); font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0.35rem 0 0.7rem 0; }

    .adjuster-claim-row { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .adjuster-claim-row select {
        background: rgba(10, 16, 28, 0.7);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.32);
        border-radius: 6px;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        min-width: 280px;
    }
    .adjuster-claim-row select:focus {
        outline: none;
        border-color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 25%, transparent);
    }
    .adjuster-secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: rgba(238, 242, 247, 0.86);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.32);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.45rem 0.85rem;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        cursor: pointer;
    }
    .adjuster-secondary:hover { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05); color: #fff; }

    .adjuster-empty { margin-top: 0.6rem; }
    .adjuster-empty a { color: var(--adjuster-accent); }

    .adjuster-claim-card {
        margin-top: 0.8rem;
        background: rgba(10, 16, 28, 0.7);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.18);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.8rem 0.95rem;
    }
    .adjuster-claim-num {
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
        color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
    }
    .adjuster-claim-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 0.4rem 0.85rem;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: rgba(238, 242, 247, 0.88);
    }
    @@media (max-width: 820px) { .adjuster-claim-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    .adjuster-claim-grid .span-2 { grid-column: span 2; }
    @@media (max-width: 820px) { .adjuster-claim-grid .span-2 { grid-column: span 1; } }
    .adjuster-claim-grid .k {
        display: inline-block;
        min-width: 110px;
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        margin-right: 0.5rem;
    }

    #adjuster-process-btn {
        background: var(--adjuster-accent);
        color: #1a1100;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        cursor: pointer;
        margin-top: 0.35rem;
    }
    #adjuster-process-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { filter: brightness(1.08); transform: translateY(-1px); }
    #adjuster-process-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }

    .adjuster-status {
        margin-top: 0.6rem; font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: rgba(238, 242, 247, 0.88);
    }
    .adjuster-status.error { color: #fca5a5; }
    .adjuster-status .spinner {
        display: inline-block; width: 12px; height: 12px;
        border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); border-top-color: #fff;
        border-radius: 50%; margin-right: 6px; vertical-align: middle;
        animation: adjuster-spin 0.7s linear infinite;
    }
    @@keyframes adjuster-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

    /* ----- Step 4: Chat with the Loss Adjuster Agent + references ------- */
    .adjuster-chat-layout {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 320px;
        gap: 0.9rem;
        margin-top: 0.6rem;
    }
    @@media (max-width: 980px) {
        .adjuster-chat-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }

    .adjuster-chat-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-width: 0; }

    .adjuster-chat-messages {
        background: rgba(10, 16, 28, 0.7);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.18);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 0.7rem 0.85rem;
        max-height: 420px;
        overflow-y: auto;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.55rem;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-empty {
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 1.2rem 0.5rem;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-msg {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        max-width: 88%;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-msg-user { align-self: flex-end; align-items: flex-end; }
    .adjuster-chat-msg-assistant { align-self: flex-start; align-items: flex-start; }
    .adjuster-chat-bubble {
        padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
        border-radius: 12px;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.45;
        word-wrap: break-word;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-msg-user .adjuster-chat-bubble {
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 26%, rgba(20, 28, 46, 0.9));
        color: #fff;
        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 50%, transparent);
        border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;
        white-space: pre-wrap;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-msg-assistant .adjuster-chat-bubble {
        background: rgba(15, 22, 38, 0.95);
        color: var(--zava-text, #e8eef9);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.22);
        border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-msg-assistant .adjuster-chat-bubble .agent-md {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-meta {
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        margin-top: 0.2rem;
    }

    .adjuster-chat-form {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.4rem;
        margin-top: 0.55rem;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-form input[type="text"] {
        flex: 1;
        background: rgba(10, 16, 28, 0.7);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.32);
        border-radius: 8px;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .adjuster-chat-form input[type="text"]:focus {
        outline: none;
        border-color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 25%, transparent);
    }
    #adjuster-chat-send {
        background: var(--adjuster-accent);
        color: #1a1100;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.55rem 1.05rem;
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        cursor: pointer;
    }
    #adjuster-chat-send:hover:not(:disabled) { filter: brightness(1.08); }
    #adjuster-chat-send:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }

    /* ----- References panel (Bing + document citations) ----------------- */
    .adjuster-refs-col {
        background: rgba(10, 16, 28, 0.6);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.18);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem;
        align-self: start;
        max-height: 480px;
        overflow-y: auto;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-head {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-head h4 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        color: #fff;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-count {
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 22%, rgba(20, 28, 46, 0.9));
        color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 45%, transparent);
        padding: 1px 8px;
        border-radius: 999px;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-help {
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        margin: 0 0 0.55rem 0;
        line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-list {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.45rem;
    }
    .adjuster-refs-empty {
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 0.8rem 0.4rem;
    }
    .adjuster-ref-card {
        background: rgba(15, 22, 38, 0.85);
        border: 1px solid rgba(120, 150, 200, 0.18);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--adjuster-accent);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.45rem 0.6rem;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .adjuster-ref-kind {
        display: inline-block;
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        padding: 1px 6px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    }
    .adjuster-ref-kind-bing {
        color: #8ab4f8;
        background: rgba(138, 180, 248, 0.12);
        border: 1px solid rgba(138, 180, 248, 0.3);
    }
    .adjuster-ref-kind-doc {
        color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 15%, transparent);
        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--adjuster-accent) 35%, transparent);
    }
    .adjuster-ref-card a {
        color: var(--adjuster-accent);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        word-break: break-word;
    }
    .adjuster-ref-card a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .adjuster-ref-url {
        display: block;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        color: var(--zava-muted, #97a3b6);
        margin-top: 0.15rem;
        word-break: break-all;
    }
</style>

